        <akn:num>28:2-705</akn:num>
        <akn:heading>Sellerâ€™s stoppage of delivery in transit or otherwise.</akn:heading>
<akn:subsection eId="subsec_28:2-705_1">
      <akn:num>(1)</akn:num>
      <akn:content><akn:p>The seller may stop delivery of goods in the possession of a carrier or other bailee when he discovers the buyer to be insolvent (section 28:2-702) and may stop delivery of carload, truckload, planeload or larger shipments of express or freight when the buyer repudiates or fails to make a payment due before delivery or if for any other reason the seller has a right to withhold or reclaim the goods.</akn:p></akn:content>
    </akn:subsection><akn:subsection eId="subsec_28:2-705_2">
